@using WebTimer.WebRole.Helpers;
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
    var isMobile = BrowserAgent.IsMobile(Request.UserAgent);
    var containerClass = isMobile ? "" : "jumbotron container main-container";
}
<div class="@containerClass">
@if (!isMobile) {
    <img class="webtimer-jumbotron" src="~/Content/images/WebTimer_logo.png" alt="WebTimer" />
    <br />
}

    <div class="list-group col-lg-3 col-md-4 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <a href="#webtimer" class="list-group-item active">WebTimer</a>
        <a href="#how" class="list-group-item">How does it work?</a>
        <a href="#privacy" class="list-group-item">Your privacy</a>
        <a href="#company" class="list-group-item">The company</a>
        <a href="#start" class="list-group-item">Getting started</a>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-content col-lg-9 col-md-8 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <div class="tab-pane active" id="webtimer">
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>
            <p>If you're like us, your kids are spending lots of time on the Web.</p>
            <p>
                The Web is great - it's an incredible and indispensable resource for our kids as they grow and mature.
                It is also increasingly how our kids socialize with others - it's impossible to be a teenager without being online.
            </p>
            <p>But too much of anything can be a bad thing, and studies have shown that spending too much time online can become unhealthy and habit-forming.</p>
            <p><i>WebTimer</i> was created to help parents get a better idea of how their kids are spending time online.</p>
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md">
                <br />
                <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Back to top</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-pane" id="how">
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>
            <p>
                <i>WebTimer</i> unobtrusively collects information from every device it is installed on.  
                It forwards this information to a cloud service.  You can sign into the <i>WebTimer</i> 
                website from any device with a browser, and view everything that's been going on.
            </p>
            <p>
                <i>WebTimer</i> automatically picks up the names of each of the devices it is installed on,
                and allows you to associate each device with a person.  This way, you can get a complete picture of 
                how each kid is spending their time on the Web.
            </p>
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md">
                <br />
                <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Back to top</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-pane" id="privacy">
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>
            <p>
                <i>WebTimer</i> treats your information with the utmost respect.  We will never sell your personal 
                information.  To anyone.  EVER.  
            </p>
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md">
                <br />
                <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Back to top</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-pane" id="company">
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>
            <p>
                <i>WebTimer LLC</i> is an early-stage startup in the beautiful Seattle area.
                It was started by two parents just like you.
            </p>
            <div class="team-members">
                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <div class="team-member-photo">
                        <a onclick="window.open('http://www.linkedin.com/in/sherigazitt')">
                            <img class="team-member-image" src="~/Content/images/sheri.png" alt="Sheri Gazitt" />
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Sheri has a Masters in Psychology and is a certified teen life coach.  She is the founder of <a onclick="window.open('http://www.teenwiseseattle.com')">Teen Wise</a> 
                        and gives talks to teens and adults in the Seattle area.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6 col-xs-12">
                    <div class="team-member-photo">
                        <a onclick="window.open('http://www.linkedin.com/in/ogazitt')">
                            <img class="team-member-image" src="~/Content/images/omri.png" alt="Omri Gazitt" />
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Omri is a software exec and the co-founder of <a onclick="window.open('http://www.builtsteady.com')">BuiltSteady</a>. 
                        He's worked on many things over his 20 year career, but considers raising his three girls to be his greatest achievement.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md">
                <br />
                <p><a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Back to top</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-pane" id="start">
            <div class="hidden-lg hidden-md"><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></div>
            <p>
                To get started, download and install the <i>WebTimer</i> software on 
                each of your devices.  The first time you install the software, you will create a <i>WebTimer</i> account.
                Alternatively, you can sign up for the service and then install the software.
            </p>
            <br />
            <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 col-sm-3 hidden-xs">
                <a href="/home/download" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Download</a>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-2 col-lg-offset-1 col-md-2 col-md-offset-1 col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-1 col-xs-4 col-xs-offset-1">
                <a href="/" class="btn btn-success btn-lg">Sign Up</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script type="text/javascript">
    $(document).ready(function () {
        $('.list-group a').click(function (e) {
            $(this).tab('show');
            $('.list-group a').removeClass('active');
            $(this).addClass('active');
        });
    });
</script>